Five armed robbers have been killed and one arrested following a shootout with police.It is reported that the shootout took place in Springfield, Durban when a group of suspects robbed business premises.Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said, &#8220;When police approached the suspects they fired shots and police had to return fire.&#8220;During the shootout between the police and the suspects one was shot and killed and the three other suspects were arrested,&#8221; he said.Zwane also indicated that five other suspects fled the scene in a getaway vehicle and police gave a chase, but the suspects continued firing at the police.&#8220;At Parlock area in Newlands, four suspects were shot and killed, one managed to escape and firearms were recovered at the scene.&#8221;-TNA Reporter 